The article is a transcript of remarks made by President Donald Trump during a celebration of the friendship between Italy and the United States. The event honored the achievements of the Italian-American community and featured special guest President Sergio Mattarella of Italy. Trump also acknowledged the contributions of Italian-Americans to various aspects of American society and culture. Mario Andretti, a legendary racecar driver, was also present and spoke briefly. President Mattarella expressed gratitude for the warm welcome and emphasized the strong bonds between the two countries. He highlighted the importance of the Trans-Atlantic Alliance and the shared values and principles between the United States and Italy. Mattarella also mentioned the cooperation in areas such as foreign policy, defense, trade, and space exploration.